V3100.example: NullReferenceException is possible when dereferencing 'GraphicsDevice' variable. Unhandled exceptions in destructor lead to termination of runtime.

V3024.example: An odd precise comparison: vector.X == 0. Consider using a comparison with defined precision: Math.Abs(A - B) < Epsilon.

V3041.example: The expression was implicitly cast from 'int' type to 'float' type. Consider utilizing an explicit type cast to avoid the loss of a fractional part. An example: double A = (double)(X) / Y;.

V3010.example: The return value of function 'Advance' is required to be utilized.

V5609.example: Possible path traversal vulnerability. Potentially tainted data from the 'file' variable is used as path.

V3063.example: A part of conditional expression is always false if it is evaluated: other.Controllers[i].Connected.

V5606.example: An empty exception handler. Silent suppression of exceptions may hide the presence of bugs or vulnerabilities.

V3072.example: The 'Page' class containing IDisposable members does not itself implement IDisposable. Inspect: image, atlas.

V3073.example: Not all IDisposable members are properly disposed. Call 'Dispose' when disposing 'Batcher' class. Inspect: mesh.

V3139.example: Two or more case-branches perform the same actions.

V3109.example: The 'interval' sub-expression is present on both sides of the operator. The expression is incorrect or it can be simplified.
